# Patterns excluded from lychee link checks.
# One entry per line — Go-style regular expressions.

# Badge/canonical URLs that may have transient network errors in CI.
https://awesome\.re/

# Intel content-delivery CDN blocks automated HTTP HEAD/GET requests.
https://www\.intel\.com/content/dam/

# Intel developer pages return 403 to automated scanners.
https://www\.intel\.com/content/www/us/en/

# Oracle blogs block automated checks.
https://blogs\.oracle\.com/

# Arm developer blogs block automated checks.
https://developer\.arm\.com/community/arm-community-blogs/

# Scaleway blog blocks automated checks.
https://www\.scaleway\.com/en/blog/

# Medium blocks automated checks on some articles.
https://medium\.com/

# Qualcomm product pages frequently restructure URLs.
https://www\.qualcomm\.com/products/

# MediaTek short URLs may not resolve reliably from CI.
https://i\.mediatek\.com/

# Google Store may redirect individual product pages.
https://store\.google\.com/
